race.comment: Hard to rule too many of these out. FOURCADE (1) led in a change of tactics last start and battled on well to hold third over 1300m at Moruya against open class sprinters. Five-time winner over this shorter trip, including two from two here. Looks a huge chance back in Benchmark company. The speedy PUSHALOT (11) has strung together three good performances, the latest over 1000m at Queanbeyan where she tried hard in front but found one better. Gets some weight relief and is suited out to this trip. Serious contender. The flying PLEASURIZE (3) missed the frame for the first time recently when reeled in at Cootamundra over 1100m. Will be hard to catch although the last 100m is the query. COSSACK WARRIOR (8) is a new Luke Pepper acquisition back from a six-month break. Distance specialist proven at this level. Should make an immediate impact for the new stable. KING CHARLES (2) races well here but needs some rain about - watch the track conditions and promote him if it deteriorates.
